<paragraph id="4A6C369CFF89FFDDFF68F8A686F089C1" blockId="1.[151,1436,1861,2023]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF89FFDDFF68F8A68679897A" bold="true" box="[199,309,1861,1884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimen examined agrees with the description by 
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF89FFDDFC04F8A683B4897A" author="Birstein" box="[939,1272,1861,1884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" refString="Birstein, J. A. &amp; Vinogradov, L. G. (1972) Craboids (Decapoda, Anomura, Lithodidae) of the Atlantic sector of the Antarctic, South America and South Africa (in Russian). Zoologicheskii Zhurnal, 51, 351 - 363." type="journal article" year="1972">
Birstein &amp; Vinogradov (
<number id="FC1B24BBFF89FFDDFB17F8A683BC897A" box="[1208,1264,1861,1884]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" value="1972.0">1972</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
except for the armature of the scaphocerite, which has two pairs of lateral spines, and in the specimen analyzed here, just one spine on the inner side. However, 
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF89FFDDFE03F86885C28984" author="Macpherson" box="[428,654,1931,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" refString="Macpherson, E. (1988 b) Revision of the Family Lithodidae Samouelle, 1819 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura) in the Atlantic Ocean. Monografias de Zoologia Marina, 2, 1 - 153." type="journal article" year="1988" yearSuffix="b">
Macpherson (
<number id="FC1B24BBFF89FFDDFDEEF86885348984" box="[577,632,1931,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240" value="1988.0">1988</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
noted that in the 
<typeStatus id="9568883EFF89FFDDFCFAF86884F98984" box="[853,949,1931,1954]" pageId="1" pageNumber="240">holotype</typeStatus>
, the inner side of the scaphocerite has three spines; this character may be variable in juvenile and adult specimens. The variations of this new specimen could be related to its juvenile stage.
</paragraph>
<caption id="1EAC6614FF8AFFDEFF38FA0387958812" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/232858/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" targetBox="[250,1331,185,1475]" targetPageId="2">
<paragraph id="4A6C369CFF8AFFDEFF38FA0387958812" blockId="2.[151,1436,1504,1588]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFF38FA0386428BD3" bold="true" box="[151,270,1504,1526]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">FIGURE 2</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFEB4FA0285428BD0" box="[283,526,1505,1526]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFEB4FA0285428BD0" box="[283,526,1505,1526]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">Paralomis spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, male, cl 13.61 mm (MACN-In 39716). A, anterior part of the carapace, dorsal view; B, anterior part of the carapace, lateral view; C, right cheliped; D, right cheliped, dorsal view; E, third left walking leg. Scale bar = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="4A6C369CFF8AFFDEFF68F9BC822688D1" blockId="2.[151,1436,1630,2009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">
The species is distinguished from all other described species of 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFCC6F9BD84948850" box="[873,984,1630,1654]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFCC6F9BD84948850" box="[873,984,1630,1654]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">Paralomis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the armature of the carapace, chelipeds and walking legs that are densely covered by acute spines. Eleven species share this character (
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF8AFFDEFB3DF963827D88B1" author="Guzman" box="[1170,1329,1664,1688]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" refString="Guzman, G. (2009) Paralomis sonne nueva especie de Litodido (Decapoda, Paguroidea, Lithodidae) en aguas profundas frente a Antofagasta, Chile. Latin American Journal Aquatic Research, 37, 1 - 5. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3856 / vol 37 - issue 2 - fulltext- 12" type="journal article" year="2009">
Guzmán 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFB57F963827D88B1" box="[1272,1329,1664,1687]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
), but only 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFF38F94286AC8891" authority="Macpherson, 1988" authorityName="Macpherson" authorityYear="1988" box="[151,480,1696,1720]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erinacea">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFF38F94286438891" box="[151,271,1696,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. erinacea</emphasis>
Macpherson, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFE07F94386AC8891" box="[424,480,1696,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1988.0">1988</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFE44F94285A48891" authority="Guzman, 2009" authorityName="Guzman" authorityYear="2009" box="[491,744,1696,1720]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonne">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFE44F942850F889E" box="[491,579,1697,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. sonne</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF8AFFDEFDE4F94385A48891" author="Guzman" box="[587,744,1696,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" refString="Guzman, G. (2009) Paralomis sonne nueva especie de Litodido (Decapoda, Paguroidea, Lithodidae) en aguas profundas frente a Antofagasta, Chile. Latin American Journal Aquatic Research, 37, 1 - 5. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3856 / vol 37 - issue 2 - fulltext- 12" type="journal article" year="2009">
Guzmán, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFD1CF94385A48891" box="[691,744,1696,1719]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
closely resemble 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFC05F94283008891" box="[938,1100,1696,1720]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFC05F94283008891" box="[938,1100,1696,1720]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
because they are more densely covered with spines than, for instance, 
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFDEBF92285F988FE" box="[580,693,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. f or m os a</emphasis>
Henderson, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFCEBF923843588F1" box="[836,889,1728,1751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1888.0">1888</number>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFC1DF92283AC88F1" authority="Hansen, 1908" authorityName="Hansen" authorityYear="1908" box="[946,1248,1727,1752]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spectabilis">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFC1DF922830C88F1" box="[946,1088,1727,1752]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spectabilis</emphasis>
Hansen, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFB07F92383AC88F1" box="[1192,1248,1728,1751]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1908.0">1908</number>
</taxonomicName>
. Moreover, these spines are not as long as in 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFE14F90285A388D1" authority="Macpherson, 1992" authorityName="Macpherson" authorityYear="1992" box="[443,751,1759,1784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phryxa">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFE14F902855388D1" box="[443,543,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. phryxa</emphasis>
Macpherson, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFD18F90385A388D1" box="[695,751,1760,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1992.0">1992</number>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFD55F902841188D1" box="[762,861,1759,1784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hystrix">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFD55F902841188D1" box="[762,861,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. hystrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(de Haan, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFC7EF903834488D1" box="[977,1032,1760,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1844.0">1844</number>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFBECF902822A88D1" authority="Sakai, 1980" authorityName="Sakai" authorityYear="1980" box="[1091,1382,1759,1784]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hystrixoides">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFBECF902839288D1" box="[1091,1246,1759,1784]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. hystrixoides</emphasis>
Sakai, 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFA81F903822A88D1" box="[1326,1382,1760,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1980.0">1980</number>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6C369CFF8AFFDEFF68F8E385B2899E" blockId="2.[151,1436,1630,2009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">
The differences between 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFE72F8E285148931" box="[477,600,1792,1816]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="erinacea">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFE72F8E285148931" box="[477,600,1792,1816]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. erinacea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFD3BF8E284758931" box="[660,825,1792,1816]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFD3BF8E284758931" box="[660,825,1792,1816]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF8AFFDEFBB8F8E383B68931" author="Macpherson" box="[1047,1274,1792,1815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" refString="Macpherson, E. (1988 b) Revision of the Family Lithodidae Samouelle, 1819 (Crustacea: Decapoda: Anomura) in the Atlantic Ocean. Monografias de Zoologia Marina, 2, 1 - 153." type="journal article" year="1988" yearSuffix="b">
Macpherson (
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFB02F8E383A88931" box="[1197,1252,1792,1815]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="1988.0">1988</number>
b)
</bibRefCitation>
and are based mainly on the presence of thick spines in the gastric and branchial regions in the latter species. Our specimen is agree with the Macpherson’s observations in the presence of thick spines in the gastric and branchial regions. On the other hand, the rostrum of 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFEDBF882855A8951" box="[372,534,1888,1912]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFEDBF882855A8951" box="[372,534,1888,1912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFD0DF88285B6895E" box="[674,762,1889,1912]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonne">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFD0DF88285B6895E" box="[674,762,1889,1912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. sonne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the shape and number of the spines; 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFB32F88283B9895E" box="[1181,1269,1889,1912]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonne">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFB32F88283B9895E" box="[1181,1269,1889,1912]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. sonne</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
bears two pairs of lateral spines and just one in 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFE5BF86385D489B1" box="[500,664,1920,1943]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFE5BF86385D489B1" box="[500,664,1920,1943]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Other differences are in the armature of the pereiopods, more densely covered in 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFEA2F84286E3899E" box="[269,431,1953,1976]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spinosissima">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFEA2F84286E3899E" box="[269,431,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. spinosissima</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
than 
<taxonomicName id="8DD34D1FFF8AFFDEFE44F84285B6899E" authority="Guzman 2009" authorityName="Guzman" authorityYear="2009" box="[491,762,1953,1977]" class="Malacostraca" family="Lithodidae" genus="Paralomis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sonne">
<emphasis id="78A7EA8EFF8AFFDEFE44F842850F899E" box="[491,579,1953,1976]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">P. sonne</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="2E424B6DFF8AFFDEFDFCF84285BE899E" author="Guzman" box="[595,754,1953,1977]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" refString="Guzman, G. (2009) Paralomis sonne nueva especie de Litodido (Decapoda, Paguroidea, Lithodidae) en aguas profundas frente a Antofagasta, Chile. Latin American Journal Aquatic Research, 37, 1 - 5. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3856 / vol 37 - issue 2 - fulltext- 12" type="journal article" year="2009">
Guzmán 
<number id="FC1B24BBFF8AFFDEFD17F84285BE899E" box="[696,754,1953,1976]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241" value="2009.0">2009</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4A6C369CFF8AFFDEFF68F821826689FF" blockId="2.[151,1436,1630,2009]" box="[199,1322,1986,2009]" pageId="2" pageNumber="241">The present specimen from Mar del Plata extends significantly the distribution of the species northwards.</paragraph>
